parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflators can cause serious or fatal injuries due to the rupture of the inflators during deployment.
symptoms: as the issue is related to a potential failure of the airbag inflators in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can compromise the deployment of the airbags, potentially causing serious or fatal injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Cracking of the dashboard around the passenger airbag deployment area
above the top of the driver-side instrument panel
and in other areas of the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can cause sharp edges, debris, and shrapnel to be thrown into the cabin in the event of an airbag deployment, potentially causing injury or death to vehicle occupants.
symptoms: often near the passenger airbag or instrument panel
with no apparent reason or incident; dashboard vibrates while driving; loud distracting noise; and sharp edges resulting from cracking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake oil leaking; master cylinder leak; brake pedal feels soft or spongy; brake pedal sticks to the floor; brake pedal does not return to its normal position; brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position; brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure; vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle rolls backwards or forwards without warning; vehicle moves on its own while in park or neutral gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission system can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls without warning; vehicle loses power; gear shifter acts like it is stuck; vehicle will not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls without warning; vehicle loses power; locks
and front lights start to go off and on; complete loss of acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can cause a safety hazard in the event of an airbag deployment, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities. Additionally, the cracking can create sharp edges and flying debris, which can cause harm to occupants.
symptoms: often near the airbag or instrument cluster
which can spread over time. The cracks can be small or large
and may appear suddenly or gradually.
